Package: Texevier
Type: Package
Title: Template for Formal Research Papers with the 'Elsevier' 'Latex' Format
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Nico", "Katzke", email = "nfkatzke@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Maintainer: Nico Katzke <nfkatzke@gmail.com>
Depends:
    R (>= 3.4.0)
BugReports: https://github.com/nicktz/Texevier/issues
Imports:
    dplyr,
    ggplot2,
    rmarkdown,
    knitr,
    xtable,
    huxtable
Description: Provides users with a quick means of setting up a folder that produces 
     an academic paper having the 'Elsevier' format. Users will have to have
     'Latex' installed first, as well as 'rmarkdown' and 'Rstudio'. I recommend 
     installing Yihui Xie's tinytex first.
License: GPL-3
SystemRequirements: LaTeX
LazyData: TRUE
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
Repository: CRAN
NeedsCompilation: yes
ByteCompile: yes
VignetteBuilder: knitr
